		    </div>

		    <h3>Director of Culture, Jake Colavolpe</h3>
		    <div class="row">
		    	<div class="col-md-6">
		    		<%= image_tag 'IMG_7522.jpg' %>
		    	</div>

		    	<div class="col-md-6">
		    		<p>Jake Colavolpe is a freshman in Morse College intending to double major in WGSS and Sociology. Jake began his involvement with MUN in high school, through YIRA’s Hemipheres program. He loves teaching, being both an instructor for Hemispheres and the head debate coach for Wilbur Cross High School in New Haven. Jake is thrilled to be the Director of Culture of this year’s YMUNI. He looks forward to helping to reshape MUN life and cutlure through YMUNI 2015!</p>
		    	</div>
		    </div>

		    <h3>KJ Ong, Director of Conference & Delegate Affairs</h3>
		    <div class="row">
		    	<div class="col-md-6">
		    		<%= image_tag 'IMG_7513.jpg' %>
		    	</div>

		    	<div class="col-md-6">
		    		<p>KJ Ong is a Malaysian sophomore in Berkeley College majoring in History. His academic interests are democracy movements against authoritarian states, ethnic conflict & genocide, and digital humanities. Prior to coming to Yale, KJ took a gap year in his home country, working for a think tank, a political party, a human rights lawyers organization, and a coalition of democracy activists. At Yale, KJ was the Director General of Committees for Yale Model United Nations XLI, the Community Secretary of the Liberal Party of the Yale Political Union, and the Outreach Director of the Yale Gamers Club. He is deeply passionate about connecting real world issues to everyday classroom experiences, and is extremely excited to see all of you at YMUNI! </p>
		    	</div>
		    </div>

		    <h3>Miranda Melcher, Director of Curriculum</h3>
