		    	</div>

		    	<div class="col-md-6">
		    		<p>Miranda Melcher is a rising senior in Branford College at Yale University and is this year’s Director of Curriculum for YMUNI. Miranda is a political science major, studying on civil wars in the Middle East and Africa. Miranda grew up as an expat in Beijing, China, where she attended international school and many MUN conferences. Outside of YMUNI, Miranda is involved with YMUN, YMUN Korea, Hemispheres, Jewish life at Yale, and a member of the Yale Political Union. Miranda sees YMUNI as a great opportunity to work with exceptional high school students and way to give back her years of IR and MUN knowledge. Please do not hesitate to reach out to Miranda with any questions at teach.ymuni@yira.org.</p>
